task_context.background_context:
Creating quiz questions for PSYC100 General Psychology course. Questions must follow this JSON format:
{
  "question": "Question text?",
  "difficulty": "learning|application|tricky",
  "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"],
  "answer": "Exact correct option text",
  "explanation": {
    "correct": "Why this is right",
    "incorrect": {
      "Option A": "Why wrong",
      "Option B": "Why wrong",
      "Option C": "Why wrong"
    }
  }
}

Week 6 (Perception) covers: Gestalt principles (figure-ground, proximity, closure, similarity, continuity, symmetry), depth perception (monocular/binocular cues, pictorial cues), perceptual constancy, visual illusions, Gregory's constructivist vs Gibson's ecological theory.

Week 7 (Social Psychology) covers: Attribution (internal/external), Heider's naive scientist, Jones & Davis correspondence inference, Kelley's covariation theory (consensus, distinctiveness, consistency), attribution biases (FAE, false consensus, self-serving, actor-observer), conformity (Sherif, Asch), obedience (Milgram, Zimbardo).

Week 8 (Developmental) covers: Attachment (Harlow, Bowlby, Ainsworth Strange Situation, 4 attachment styles), self-concept development, Piaget's cognitive stages (sensorimotor, preoperational, concrete operational, formal operational), assimilation/accommodation, Vygotsky's ZPD.

Week 9 (Intelligence) covers: Spearman's g factor, Cattell's fluid/crystallized intelligence, Sternberg's triarchic theory, Gardner's multiple intelligences, IQ tests (Stanford-Binet, Wechsler, Raven's), gender/racial IQ differences, Flynn effect, heredity vs environment.
